## What Is a 4 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring?

A 4 carat cushion cut diamond ring centres a 4ct cushion-shaped diamond — approximately 10mm × 10mm in standard square proportions — in an engagement ring setting. At 4ct, the cushion cut enters territory that most buyers never encounter in a retailer's display case. The face-up area at 4ct is approximately 100mm² versus 81mm² at 3ct — a 23% increase that, combined with the jump from 9mm to 10mm diameter, transforms the ring from "dramatic" to "exceptional." A 4ct cushion ring does not merely draw attention; it commands it.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [4 carat cushion cut](/cushion-cut-diamond) occupies a singular position in the diamond market: the size at which the natural inventory collapses into The Empty Tier, the size at which The Pillow Premium reaches its steepest absolute expression in dollar terms, and the size at which the financial case for lab over natural becomes so overwhelming that it requires an explicit values-based argument to justify purchasing natural. A buyer who arrives at 4ct without understanding these three realities is not equipped to make a sound purchase decision.

What determines whether a 4ct cushion purchase succeeds: understanding The Empty Tier before expecting to shop and compare natural options, understanding that the modified brilliant's Crushed Ice Trap — covered in detail in the [3 carat cushion cut diamond ring guide](/3-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) — becomes even more consequential at 4ct face-up, and understanding that VS1 clarity is the minimum for natural 4ct stones where video verification of VS2 becomes unreliable at this face-up size.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

