## The Pillow Premium

The Pillow Premium — the systematic cost premium that cushion cuts carry over princess cuts of equivalent quality — reaches its steepest absolute expression at 4ct. At 2ct, The Pillow Premium adds $1,500–$2,500 over a comparable princess. At 3ct, it adds $4,000–$6,000. At 4ct natural, where a GIA F-VS1 princess of comparable quality typically runs $55,000–$65,000, the cushion F-VS1 is $85,685 — a premium of $20,000–$30,000 for the same colour, clarity, and certification in a cushion shape.

[![Cushion cut diamond engagement ring yellow gold solitaire on white background](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/505021/505021_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

The demand mechanism driving The Pillow Premium at 4ct is the same as at smaller sizes — cushion cuts are preferred by more buyers than princess cuts, so cushion rough commands a higher per-carat price — but the absolute dollar premium scales with the carat price, which itself scales non-linearly at 4ct. A single dollar-per-carat premium at 4ct is four times the absolute dollar premium of the same per-carat premium at 1ct. This is why the abstract concept of The Pillow Premium becomes a concrete, unavoidable line item at 4ct in a way that it is merely an interesting observation at smaller sizes.

**In the lab market at 4ct, The Pillow Premium disappears entirely.** Lab production of 4ct cushion modified brilliants is abundant — the BN lab 4ct cushion table contains GIA and IGI options at identical price points, with no premium for the cushion shape over comparable lab princess cuts. The $7,412 lab GIA D-VVS1 cushion is priced identically to lab GIA D-VVS1 rounds at 4ct from the same retailer. At 4ct lab, shape is purely an aesthetic choice with no pricing consequence.

For the full trajectory of The Pillow Premium from 2ct through 3ct, see the [2 carat cushion cut diamond ring guide](/2-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) and the [3 carat cushion cut diamond ring guide](/3-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) where this concept is traced across the natural market's price escalation.

