## The Empty Tier

The Empty Tier is the defining market reality of the 4ct natural cushion segment — and it is the most important concept any natural 4ct cushion buyer must understand before beginning their search.

[![Cushion cut diamond engagement ring in rose gold solitaire with pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/502250/502250_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**What The Empty Tier means in practice.** At Blue Nile, the natural GIA cushion inventory at common carat weights looks like this: 1ct — dozens of options. 2ct — eight stones. 3ct — seven stones. 4ct — three stones. This is not a function of Blue Nile's inventory management or purchasing strategy; it is a function of natural diamond supply. Large natural rough crystals that yield a 4ct+ cushion shape after cutting are rare. The proportion of natural rough that produces a well-cut 4ct cushion modified brilliant at GIA F-VS1 or better quality is a fraction of the already-rare supply of 4ct+ natural rough. What you see on Blue Nile at any given time is essentially the global retail supply of GIA-certified 4ct cushion modified brilliants at Ideal cut quality.

**The pricing consequence.** When there are three competing natural 4ct cushion stones, there is no meaningful competition between them on price. Retailers price 4ct natural cushions based on rarity, not competitive positioning. The buyer cannot comparison-shop effectively because there is nothing to compare. The $85,685 entry is what is available — if that stone is sold when you visit the site, you may be looking at a zero-stone market in that tier for days or weeks. This is structurally unlike shopping at 2ct or 3ct, where buyers can compare quality and price across multiple options.

**The buyer's strategic response to The Empty Tier.** If you are committed to a natural 4ct cushion, buy the stone when it is available and meets your requirements. Do not wait for "a better stone to appear" — one may not appear for an extended period. Do not hold out for a price negotiation — the retailer has no competitive pressure to reduce price on a stone with no comparable substitute in the same market. Do not expect the same browsing and comparison experience you had at 2ct or 3ct. The Empty Tier buyer must be decisive.

**The Empty Tier in the lab market.** The Empty Tier does not exist in the lab 4ct cushion market. Blue Nile's lab 4ct cushion inventory includes dozens of options at D-VVS1 through D-FL quality with both GIA and IGI certification. Lab buyers at 4ct can browse, compare, wait, and choose — the full conventional diamond shopping experience. This asymmetry between natural and lab at 4ct is more dramatic than at any smaller carat weight and is the clearest argument for lab at the 4ct tier.

