**Reading the natural table.** Three rows. That is The Empty Tier. The entry stone — [GIA 4.04ct F-VS1 Ideal at $85,685](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28281344?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — is the only natural 4ct cushion available under $100,000. F colour is near-colourless and will read as visually colourless in yellow or rose gold; in platinum or white gold, F at 4ct face-up shows minimal warmth but may not read as perfectly colourless to a trained eye in direct comparison with D-E stones. VS1 clarity at 4ct in a cushion modified brilliant is the practical minimum for eye-cleanliness without video verification — unlike VS2, which requires HD video confirmation at this size.

**Natural 4ct colour and clarity guidance.** At $85,685 for F-VS1 entry, the colour hierarchy at 4ct natural means: E colour ($111,144) adds $25,459 over F for one grade improvement that is invisible to the naked eye in any metal. D colour at 4ct natural GIA Ideal cushion, if available, would run $120,000–$180,000 — a price that demands a specific, examined philosophical commitment to the colour grade on paper rather than visible colour in the stone. G colour, which remains the value-maximum choice at 2ct and 3ct natural, is not available in BN's current 4ct GIA cushion Ideal inventory — a characteristic of The Empty Tier.

> "The Empty Tier changes how I advise buyers at the 4ct natural cushion level. At 2ct and 3ct, I can tell a buyer to shop around, compare several GIA stones, wait for a better option. At 4ct natural cushion, there is no 'around' — there are three stones. The advice changes: if you find a natural 4ct GIA cushion Ideal that passes your video verification, that matches your colour and clarity requirements, and that you can afford — buy it. Don't wait for the next one. There may not be a next one for months.
>
> The Empty Tier is not a flaw in the market. It is the market telling you the truth about how rare natural 4ct cushion rough actually is." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

