## 4ct Cushion Cut Diamond Clarity: Why VS1 Is the New VS2

Clarity grade selection at 4ct cushion is meaningfully different from the guidance at 2ct and 3ct — and the common advice to use the modified brilliant's light scattering to justify lower clarity grades is more dangerous at 4ct than at any smaller size.

[![Cushion cut diamond solitaire engagement ring white gold pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501590/501590_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box5_001_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**Why VS2 fails at 4ct.** At 10mm face-up, a VS2-grade inclusion in a cushion modified brilliant occupies a larger absolute area than the same VS2 grade at smaller sizes. The cushion modified brilliant's crushed ice pattern scatters light effectively at 9mm and below; at 10mm, the increased surface area means inclusions positioned near the table can become visible at normal viewing distances even when the crushed ice pattern is present. The "modified brilliant hides inclusions" generalisation, which is largely true at 1ct–3ct, becomes unreliable at 4ct. VS2 cushion modified brilliant stones at 4ct require HD video confirmation, expert review of the GIA plot, and ideally an examination of inclusion type — needle inclusions are more forgiving than cloud or crystal inclusions at this size.

**VS1 is the practical minimum at 4ct natural cushion.** VS1 inclusions in a 4ct cushion modified brilliant are reliably not visible to the naked eye under normal viewing conditions. The larger face-up area at 4ct does not compromise VS1 eye-cleanliness in the same way it compromises VS2. If you are purchasing a natural 4ct cushion — which means you are spending $85,685 or more — there is no financial logic in compromising to VS2 clarity to save $5,000–$10,000 on a $85,000+ purchase. The GIA 4ct F-VS1 at $85,685 is the natural entry and it is already at VS1.

**Clarity in the lab 4ct market.** The clarity question dissolves in the lab market: D-VVS1 at $7,412 is the entry grade. There is no financial reason to consider VS2 or SI1 in a lab 4ct cushion when VVS1 is available at $7,412. The $10,186 step to D-IF is certificatory, not visible. Buy D-VVS1 GIA and spend the saving on the setting.

**The Crushed Ice Trap at 4ct.** The crushed ice pattern's fire-hiding effect, identified at 3ct, is even more pronounced at 4ct face-up. At 10mm, the modified brilliant's uniform light distribution creates a stone that appears maximally bright — which is desirable if brightness is the goal, and deeply disappointing if visible fire was the expectation. At 4ct, the choice between cushion modified brilliant (crushed ice, brightness) and cushion brilliant (larger facets, visible fire) is the most consequential aesthetic decision in the purchase. Always verify via the HD 360° video which sub-type you are buying and confirm the visual character matches your expectation.

