## 4ct Elongated Cushion Cut Diamond Ring

The 4ct elongated cushion cut diamond ring — length-to-width ratio of 1.15:1 to 1.30:1, approximately 11mm × 9mm — is the sub-type within the 4ct tier that delivers the most dramatic visual impact relative to face-up area. At 11mm long and 9mm wide, a 4ct elongated cushion covers more finger length than any comparable square stone and reads closer to a 5ct square cushion in terms of perceived size on the hand.

At 4ct elongated cushion, the face-up silhouette creates a finger-lengthening effect that square cushions and rounds do not. For buyers with longer fingers (ring size 7 or above), the elongated cushion at 4ct is proportionally balanced and does not overhang finger edges. For buyers with shorter fingers, the elongated 4ct cushion may appear very large along the finger's length while remaining well-contained in width — a distinctive look that reads intentional rather than excessive.

The Crushed Ice Trap applies with equal force to 4ct elongated cushions: the elongated modified brilliant distributes light across a larger surface in the elongated axis, further fragmenting the already-small individual light returns. At 4ct elongated, fire is even less visible than in a square 4ct modified brilliant. Buyers who want the elongated cushion specifically for its large, elongated appearance and who prioritise the photogenic brightness of the crushed ice pattern should select the modified brilliant with confidence. Buyers who want fire in an elongated format at 4ct should request the elongated cushion brilliant sub-type and budget for VS1 or above clarity. For the complete elongated sub-type analysis, see the [elongated cushion cut diamond guide](/elongated-cushion-cut-diamond).

