## Final Verdict: Which 4ct Cushion Ring Is Right for You?

**Buy the [GIA 4ct D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified Lab at $7,412](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25222994?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) if:** You want the best single purchase in the 4ct cushion market — GIA certification, D colour, VVS1 clarity, Ideal cut, 10mm face-up impact, and $7,412 total stone cost. Set in platinum or white gold solitaire or pavé shank. The D colour reads as absolute top quality in white metal at 10mm. No verification required for clarity — VVS1 is reliably clean at every size. This is the clear recommendation for the 4ct cushion market.

**Buy the [GIA 3.96ct D-FL Ideal Cushion Modified Lab at $22,931](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27421366?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) if:** You want the absolute top GIA-certified grade combination — D colour, FL clarity — and the GIA documentation of FL matters for insurance, resale, or personal preference. Note: FL clarity at 4ct in a modified brilliant is visually identical to VVS1. The $15,519 premium over the D-VVS1 purchases the "Flawless" word on the certificate, not a visible quality improvement. This is the certificatory premium choice.

**Buy the [GIA 4.04ct F-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified Natural at $85,685](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28281344?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) if:** You have a specific, examined, and non-negotiable preference for natural origin that you can defend against $78,273 in alternative spending. Buy when it is in stock — The Empty Tier means availability is intermittent. Set in yellow gold to maximise F colour's visual performance. This is a rare stone: one of approximately three natural GIA 4ct Ideal cushions available globally in retail at any given time.

**Buy a 4ct Cushion Brilliant (non-modified) if:** You specifically want visible fire — distinct rainbow flashes under variable lighting — rather than the crushed ice uniformity of the modified brilliant at 10mm face-up. The cushion brilliant (cert reads "Cushion" not "Cushion Modified") produces distinct, directional fire flashes at 4ct that the modified brilliant cannot. Budget for VS1 or above clarity in a cushion brilliant at 4ct, verify via HD video that individual fire flashes are visible, and understand that the cushion brilliant at 4ct is rarer in retail inventory than the modified brilliant.

---

## Expert Summary

The 4 carat cushion cut diamond ring is defined by two realities that converge at this size and create a purchasing environment unlike any smaller carat weight: The Empty Tier, where natural 4ct cushion inventory collapses to three stones, and The Pillow Premium at its steepest expression, where the cushion's shape premium adds $20,000–$30,000 over a comparable princess cut at 4ct natural quality.

For lab buyers, the 4ct cushion is the most accessible luxury purchase in the diamond market: $7,412 for a GIA D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified delivers 10mm face-up presence and top certification at a total ring cost under $10,000. The financial case for lab over natural at 4ct is $78,273 — the clearest, most unambiguous number in the cushion cluster and the number that defines the 4ct tier as the lab market's strongest argument. For natural buyers with examined commitment to mined origin: understand The Empty Tier before you begin, buy when a qualifying stone is available, and do not wait for a better option that may not appear.

The recommended purchase for most buyers: [GIA 4ct D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified Lab at $7,412](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25222994?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). For natural buyers with explicit commitment: [GIA 4.04ct F-VS1 Ideal at $85,685](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28281344?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) when in stock.

Full methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

